# Rasm Dependencies

## C# central package management

- Versions live in `Directory.Packages.props`; `.csproj` files declare usage without versions.
- Check truth: `rg -n "<PackageId>" Directory.Packages.props Directory.Build.props **/*.csproj`
- Add `PackageVersion` only with a concrete consumer.
- Validate removals with `dotnet restore Workspace.slnx --locked-mode`; use normal restore for graph changes.
- Reconcile manifest edits with `docs/system-api-map/packages.md` and any affected `docs/external-libs/**/api.md` or `docs/testing-libs/**/api.md` version pins.
- `global.json` is currently absent. If introduced later, treat it as a full-static trigger.

## Host References

RhinoWIP, GH2, Eto, Rhino.UI, and RhinoWIP-hosted `System.Drawing.Common` resolve through `Directory.Build.props` app-bundle paths. Do not replace host assemblies with broad NuGet references unless `docs/system-api-map` documents the boundary.

## External-lib-first

- Approved manifest deps are first-class — integrate native APIs end-to-end
- Check `docs/system-api-map` before `System.*` additions
- Check `docs/external-libs` before LanguageExt/Thinktecture/MathNet usage
- Never hand-roll what approved libraries own; never thin-wrap external APIs

## TypeScript Catalog

Use `pnpm-workspace.yaml` catalog entries and `"catalog:"` package references. Validate with `pnpm install` and the relevant Nx typecheck target when TypeScript changes.
